            <p>
              <span class="italic">Round Rock/Georgetown:</span> We are targeting local environmental groups for an educational presentation on carbon fee and dividend that we are planning.
            </p>
            <p>
              <span class="italic">Barton Springs:</span> Our goal for the next month is for each member to consider and if able participate/create/plan two CCL focused actions.
            </p>
            <p>
              <span class="italic">Central:</span> Central's very own Susan Adams has become CCL 3rd Coast Regional Coordinator. Congrats Susan!
            </p>
            <p>
              <span class="italic">San Marcos:</span> Sarah presented on campus engagement at the regional conference, and the chapter will be working to grow engagement from TX State students as the semester has begun.
            </p>
            <p>
              <span class="italic">West/Central:</span> Our group continues to develop and evolve. Roxanne Cook has "retired" as our liaison. She is passing the baton to Mark Warren and Will Archer, who will be co-liaisons. We so appreciate Roxanne's work as liaison, including traveling to Washington D.C. last June for lobby day. We are also proud of Shalmali for this newsletter! And we were happy to welcome two new faces at our January monthly meeting.
            </p>
